{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:51:57.418687+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I'm unable to modify the issue due to insufficient permissions (read-only access token). Here's my triage summary:\n\n---\n\n## Triage Summary for Issue #1\n\n**Issue:** GIF output quality is washed out / banded compared to gifski or manual two-pass ffmpeg pipelines.\n\n**Finding:** This is a **known limitation**, explicitly documented in the codebase:\n\n- **`profiles.toml`** (lines under `[gif]`) states: *\"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"*\n\n- **`src/vidpack/runner.py`** confirms: the gif path runs a single ffmpeg call with `fps` + `scale` filters (lanczos), but no `palettegen`/`paletteuse` two-pass workflow.\n\n**Recommended action:**  \n- **Keep open** as a valid enhancement request. The issue correctly identifies the root cause (single-pass vs. two-pass palette generation) and matches the existing \"tracked in issue tracker\" note in `profiles.toml`.  \n- Apply labels `enhancement` and `known-limitation`.  \n- Optionally pin a comment confirming this is tracked and providing the manual two-pass workaround (see my attempted comment above).\n\nI was unable to perform the comment or labeling actions due to a read-only access token, but the issue is legitimate and should remain open for future resolution.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 327, "prompt_tokens": 10818, "total_tokens": 11145, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 21, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10624}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null,